if-else in Solidity
ðŸ”¹ Definition

if-else is a conditional statement used to execute code based on conditions.

Similar to other programming languages (C, C++, Java, etc.).

ðŸ”¹ Key Points

if checks a boolean condition (true/false).

else if allows multiple conditions.

else runs when none of the above are true.

Conditions use operators like ==, !=, <, >, <=, >=, &&, ||.

Often used in decision-making (e.g., access control, logic checks).

âœ… Quick Summary

if â†’ runs when condition is true.

else if â†’ additional conditions.

else â†’ default case if all fail.



